fields.descriptive_line: Album containing 32 leaves on which are pasted 46 early 18th-century trunk lining papers. Assembled in 1893 by John Eliot Hodgkin
fields.physical_description: Album of 32 leaves bound in boards covered with a coloured and gilt 18th-century 'Ausburg' paper with a design of animals, now much faded. The paper used to cover the front and back was originally one pice that was cut into two pieces: you can see where the design continues.
fields.dimensions: Height: 33 cm, Width: 21.5 cm, Depth: 2 cm
